A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending LaVeda Bennett; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, LaVeda Bennett has dedicated her life to service, demonstrating exceptional
3 commitment to her country, her fellow veterans, and her community throughout her
4 distinguished career and advocacy efforts; and
5 WHEREAS, born in Chicago to renowned guitarist Wayne Bennett and evangelist Pravella
6 Washington, she graduated from William Anderson Bass High School in Atlanta in 1976;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, she enlisted in the United States Marine Corps a day before her 20th birthday,
9 serving for 20 years and participating in major conflicts while excelling as a member of the
10 All-Marine Women's Softball Team and the Commander's Bowling Teams; and
11 WHEREAS, a tireless advocate for veterans, she has dedicated innumerable hours of her
12 time and energy toward the Atlanta VA Women's Wellness Clinic, serving as the Volunteer
13 Representative for Women Veterans, and she played a pivotal role in DeKalb County's
14 proclamation of "She Served Too," recognizing the contributions of women veterans; and
